abstract: Republican Donald Trump is touting tax cuts and economic gains during his presidency as a reason why he should get re-elected in November.
snippet: Republican Donald Trump is touting tax cuts and economic gains during his presidency as a reason why he should get re-elected in November.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Republican Donald Trump is touting tax cuts and economic gains during his presidency as a reason why he should get re-elected in November.
headline_main: As Trump Touts Gains in Jobs, Some Democrats Push for Economic Overhaul
headline_print_headline: As Trump Touts Gains in Jobs, Some Democrats Push for Economic Overhaul

abstract: When U.S. presidential candidate Joe Biden went to an Iowa university to campaign this week, one thing was in short supply: students who support him.
snippet: When U.S. presidential candidate Joe Biden went to an Iowa university to campaign this week, one thing was in short supply: students who support him.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa — When U.S. presidential candidate Joe Biden went to an Iowa university to campaign this week, one thing was in short supply: students who support him.
headline_main: Biden's Final Iowa Drive Sweeps Through Rival Territory
headline_print_headline: Biden's Final Iowa Drive Sweeps Through Rival Territory

abstract: Readers react to Bret Stephens’s argument that the Democrats’ far-left candidates are as “reckless” as the president, leaving “none of the above” as a viable option.

snippet: In normal years, Iowa is the center of the political universe during the final stretch before its famed caucuses. Top candidates rumble across the state on multi-city bus tours and hold giant rallies every night. Images of the state's snowy landsc...
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — In normal years, Iowa is the center of the political universe during the final stretch before its famed caucuses. Top candidates rumble across the state on multi-city bus tours and hold giant rallies every night. Images of the state's snowy landscape flood television screens.

abstract: As Mr. Biden campaigned in the state, residents appeared unmoved: “I don’t think much about anything Joni Ernst says.”
snippet: As Mr. Biden campaigned in the state, residents appeared unmoved: “I don’t think much about anything Joni Ernst says.”
lead_paragraph: MUSCATINE, Iowa — Senator Joni Ernst of Iowa, a Republican, wondered aloud about her Democratic constituents as they wrestled with a final decision before the looming Iowa caucuses, particularly those considering supporting former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr.

lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Tuesday seized on comments by Senator Joni Ernst, Republican of Iowa, who suggested that the White House’s arguments at the impeachment trial could hurt his political fortunes.
headline_main: In Iowa, Biden seizes on Republican senator’s comments.

abstract: In separate comments, Ms. Ernst said that she thought the White House counsel’s presentation “opened the eyes” of Iowans.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. State Department removed a National Public Radio reporter from the press pool for Secretary of State Mike Pompeo's upcoming foreign trip, a press association and NPR said on Monday, days after Pompeo angrily responded to another NPR journalist's interview with him.
